image = cv2.imread("../pics/elephant.jpg", cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
# cv2.IMREAD_COLOR : Loads a color image. Any transparency of image will be neglected. It is the default flag.
# cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE : Loads image in grayscale mode
# cv2.IMREAD_UNCHANGED : Loads image as such including alpha channel
print ("shapes of image", image.shape, " size: ", len(image.shape))

plt.imshow(image, "gray")
plt.show()

# vertical flip
new_image = image[:,::-1]
plt.imshow(new_image, "gray")
plt.show()

# horizontal flip
new_image = image[::-1,:]
plt.imshow(new_image, "gray")
plt.show()

shapes of image (600, 600)  size:  2

image = cv2.imread("../pics/elephant.jpg", cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)
# cv2.IMREAD_COLOR : Loads a color image. Any transparency of image will be neglected. It is the default flag.
# cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE : Loads image in grayscale mode
# cv2.IMREAD_UNCHANGED : Loads image as such including alpha channel
print ("shapes of image", image.shape, " size: ", len(image.shape))

b,g,r = cv2.split(image)
image = cv2.merge((r,g,b))

plt.imshow(image)
plt.show()

# vertical flip
new_image = image[:,::-1]
plt.imshow(new_image)
plt.show()

# horizontal flip
new_image = image[::-1,:]
plt.imshow(new_image)
plt.show()

# origin flip
new_image = image[::-1, ::-1]
plt.imshow(new_image)
plt.show()

shapes of image (600, 600, 3)  size:  3

def inverseImage1(image):
    w = image.shape[0]
    h = image.shape[1]
    
    if (len(image.shape) == 3):
        colored = True
        # b,g,r = cv2.split(image)
        # cMax = [np.amax(b),np.amax(g),np.amax(r)] # can be used instead 
        cMax = [0,0,0]
        for i in range(w):
            for j in range(h):
                if cMax[0] < image[i,j][0]: cMax[0] = image[i,j][0];
                if cMax[1] < image[i,j][1]: cMax[1] = image[i,j][1];
                if cMax[2] < image[i,j][2]: cMax[2] = image[i,j][2];
    else:
        colored = False
        pMax = np.uint8(np.amax(image))
        print ("max value: ", pMax)
    
    for i in range(w):
        for j in range(h):
            if not colored:
                image[i,j] = np.uint8(pMax - image[i,j])
            else:
                image[i,j][0] = np.uint8(cMax[0] - image[i,j][0])
                image[i,j][1] = np.uint8(cMax[1] - image[i,j][1])
                image[i,j][2] = np.uint8(cMax[2] - image[i,j][2])

    return image

def inverseImage2(image):
    w = image.shape[0]
    h = image.shape[1]
    
    if (len(image.shape) == 3):
        colored = True
        b,g,r = cv2.split(image)
        cMax = [np.amax(b),np.amax(g),np.amax(r)]
    else:
        colored = False
        pMax = np.uint8(np.amax(image))
        print ("max value: ", pMax)
    
    for i in range(w):
        for j in range(h):
            if not colored:
                image[i,j] = np.uint8(pMax - image[i,j])
            else:
                image[i,j][0] = np.uint8(cMax[0] - image[i,j][0])
                image[i,j][1] = np.uint8(cMax[1] - image[i,j][1])
                image[i,j][2] = np.uint8(cMax[2] - image[i,j][2])

    return image

def imageCVtoPlot(image):
    b,g,r = cv2.split(image)
    image = cv2.merge((r,g,b))
    return image

imageGray = cv2.imread("../pics/elephant.jpg", cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
imageColor = cv2.imread("../pics/elephant.jpg", cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)

plt.imshow(imageGray, "gray")
plt.show()

inverseImage2(imageGray)
plt.imshow(imageGray, "gray")
plt.show()


plt.imshow(imageCVtoPlot(imageColor))
plt.show()


e1 = cv2.getTickCount()
inverseImage1(imageColor)
e2 = cv2.getTickCount()
time = (e2 - e1)/ cv2.getTickFrequency()
print ("first with loops: ",time , "second")
plt.imshow(imageCVtoPlot(imageColor))
plt.show()

e1 = cv2.getTickCount()
inverseImage2(imageColor)
e2 = cv2.getTickCount()
time = (e2 - e1)/ cv2.getTickFrequency()
print ("second numpy and split: ", time, "second")
plt.imshow(imageCVtoPlot(imageColor))
plt.show()

In [13]:
BLUE = [255,0,0]

img = cv2.imread("../pics/elephant.jpg")

b,g,r = cv2.split(img)
img1 = cv2.merge((r,g,b))

replicate = cv2.copyMakeBorder(img1,10,10,10,10,cv2.BORDER_REPLICATE)
reflect = cv2.copyMakeBorder(img1,10,10,10,10,cv2.BORDER_REFLECT)
reflect101 = cv2.copyMakeBorder(img1,10,10,10,10,cv2.BORDER_REFLECT_101)
wrap = cv2.copyMakeBorder(img1,10,10,10,10,cv2.BORDER_WRAP)
constant= cv2.copyMakeBorder(img1,10,10,10,10,cv2.BORDER_CONSTANT,value=BLUE)

plt.subplot(231),plt.imshow(img1,'gray'),plt.title('ORIGINAL')
plt.subplot(232),plt.imshow(replicate,'gray'),plt.title('REPLICATE')
plt.subplot(233),plt.imshow(reflect,'gray'),plt.title('REFLECT')
plt.subplot(234),plt.imshow(reflect101,'gray'),plt.title('REFLECT_101')
plt.subplot(235),plt.imshow(wrap,'gray'),plt.title('WRAP')
plt.subplot(236),plt.imshow(constant,'gray'),plt.title('CONSTANT')

plt.show()
